article.headline: George Mason 72, James Madison 64 (OT)
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- Daniel Freeman scored four of his game-high 24 points in overtime on Saturday and James Madison held George Mason scoreless in the extra period to seal a 72-64 win. Terry Reynolds made a layup with five seconds left in regulation for the Patriots to tie the game at 64 and send it into overtime. After Lamar Butler's 3-pointer for George Mason tied the game at 62, Freeman made a layup that gave the Dukes a 64-62 lead with :41 to go in regulation. Dwayne Broyles scored 19 points and Ray Barbosa had 14 for the Dukes (6-14, 3-9 Colonial Athletic Association), who held a 41-32 rebounding edge over George Mason. Jai Lewis had 19 points to pace the Patriots (14-7, 7-5), who shot just 35.4 percent compared to 51.7 percent for James Madison. Reynolds scored 15 points, Butler had 12, and Mark Davis added 11.
